race.comment: All but two are debutants, and the betting moves should provide a solid guide. But no surprise if the premier stable holds the key. ERIMAR (3) debuts and draws the paint. He was just nudged out in his recent 1000m trial, and Huxtable is engaged and is a high striker at the track. Stablemate FIELD OF CLANS (5) won her 800m trial by a big margin. Maps okay and expect a bold debut run from her as well. POWER OF ANGELINE (7) is a debutant coming off a comfortable trial win over 800m. Has to be considered as well. Ditto BOWDENE (2), who maps well, and his 1000m trial win also suggests that he'll go well.
